    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## Layerre Quick Start Guide\n\nThis is the simplest possible Layerre workflow - perfect for getting started!\n\n## What This Does\n\n1. **Create template** – Import your Canva design as a Layerre template\n2. **Create variant** – Generate a single variant with custom text and image\n3. Returns the rendered image URL\n\n### Resources\n- [Layerre Documentation](https://layerre.com/docs)\n- [Community Templates](https://github.com/layerre/layerre-n8n-workflows)",
        "height": 436,
        "width": 444
      },
      "id": "66bf87df-bc46-43a8-8ce2-426e9ce2544e",
      "name": "Quick Start Guide",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -224,
        16
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## Step 1: Create Template\n\n**Instructions:**\n1. Share your Canva design (\"Anyone with the link\"-> \"Can View\")\n2. Copy the share URL\n3. Paste it in the node below\n\n**You only need to do this once!**\n\nAfter creating the template, you can deactivate this node and reuse the template ID.",
        "height": 292,
        "width": 340,
        "color": 7
      },
      "id": "5ade827c-bf8b-4ffb-8379-a3befdcc5573",
      "name": "Step 1: Create Template",
